Honeywell Inc said its total debtrose by more than 85 pct in 1986, mainly due to its 1.02billion dlr acquisition of the Sperry Aerospace Group.    At yearend, according to the company's 1986 annual report,Honeywell's total debt stood at 1.44 billion dlrs, comparedwith 776.6 mln dlrs in 1985.    Honeywell said that if it had acquired the Sperry unit atthe beginning of 1986, its loss for the full year would havebeen 9.88 dlrs a share.    Honeywell's actual loss in 1986 was 8.33 dlrs a share. Reuter&#3;